---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout pageTitle="Privacy Policy">
  <section class="legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-date">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <h2>1. Overview</h2>
    <p>
      The Virtue Initiative is a non-profit pornography accountability
      application. This policy describes what data we collect, how we use it,
      how it is protected, and your rights regarding that data. We do not sell,
      advertise with, or monetize your personal data.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data we collect</h2>
    <p>We collect the data needed to provide the service:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Account information</strong> - your email address and an optional
        display name, provided at sign-up.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Encrypted screenshot data</strong> - screenshots and other encrypted
        monitoring batches captured by The Virtue Initiative clients installed on
        your devices. These batches may include screenshots and related encrypted
        event data.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Device metadata</strong> - the name, platform, and activity timestamps
        of each device you register.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Device and monitoring logs</strong> - unencrypted log messages sent
        by clients to report operational and accountability events, such as capture
        failures, monitoring state changes, startup/shutdown or session events, and
        similar client-reported status information.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Partner relationships</strong> - the email addresses of accountability
        partners you invite, and the permissions you grant them.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Encryption and sharing records</strong> - encrypted key material and
        related records needed to restore your encrypted data and share access with
        authorized accountability partners.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Authentication and session data</strong> - access tokens, refresh
        tokens, registered device tokens, and similar session data needed to keep
        you signed in and connect devices to your account.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Local device/browser storage</strong> - clients may store local credentials,
        encryption keys, or configuration values on your device or in your browser
        so the service can continue operating after restart.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How we use your data</h2>
    <p>We use your data to provide and secure The Virtue Initiative service:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Clients may capture screenshots, monitor device or system state, and
        send logs or encrypted batches to our servers as part of the
        accountability service.
      </li>
      <li>
        Encrypted screenshot data is stored and later delivered so you and the
        accountability partners you explicitly authorize can view it with the
        appropriate decryption keys.
      </li>
      <li>
        Unencrypted device and monitoring logs are used to show activity and
        operational status to authorized users and partners.
      </li>
      <li>
        Account, device, partner, and session data is used to authenticate you,
        operate registered clients, and manage sharing permissions.
      </li>
      <li>
        We do not use your screenshots or logs for advertising, profiling, or
        model training.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      We do not currently offer self-service retention controls or promise
      automatic deletion after a fixed number of days. Data is retained while
      needed to operate the service unless and until it is deleted by us as part
      of maintenance or in response to a deletion request. You may request
      deletion of your account and associated data by contacting us at
      <a href="mailto:help@virtueinitiative.org">help@virtueinitiative.org</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data sharing</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell your personal data. We share your data only as needed to
      operate the service, including with accountability partners you explicitly
      authorize and with infrastructure providers that host or deliver service
      data. We use Cloudflare infrastructure, including Workers, D1, and R2
      object storage, and Cloudflare's own privacy policy governs their handling
      of infrastructure-level data.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Security</h2>
    <p>
      Data is transmitted over HTTPS. Encrypted screenshot batches are encrypted
      client-side before upload. Those encrypted blobs may be retrievable from
      storage if their URLs are known, but they are intended to be unreadable
      without the relevant encryption keys. Device and monitoring logs, account
      records, partner records, and other service metadata are stored
      server-side and are intended to be accessible only through authorized
      account access. Passwords are hashed and are not stored in plaintext.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Children</h2>
    <p>
      The Virtue Initiative is not intended for use by individuals under the age
      of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal
      data at any time by contacting us at
      <a href="mailto:help@virtueinitiative.org">help@virtueinitiative.org</a>.
      We will make reasonable efforts to respond within 30 days.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be
      communicated by updating the "Last updated" date above. Continued use of
      the service after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For privacy-related questions or requests, contact us at
      <a href="mailto:help@virtueinitiative.org">help@virtueinitiative.org</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
